# Group Tasks

## Tasks collection [/api/{version}/tasks{?email}{?token}{?page}{?per_page}{?completed}{?assigned_user_id}{?included_orderstatus_ids}{?taskable_type}{?taskable_id}{?due_after}{?due_before}]
Actions on the Tasks resource

+ Parameters

    + version (required, string, `v1`) - API version.
    + email (required, string, `test@example.com`) - User email
    + token (required, string, `1dofnewoi233`) - Login token
    + page (optional, integer) - Number of page.
        + Default: `1`
    + per_page (optional, integer) - Number of tasks per page.
        + Default: `25`
    + completed (optional, boolean) - Filter on task's completed flag.
    + assigned_user_id (optional, integer) - Filter on task's assigned user.
    + included_orderstatus_ids (optional, string) - Comma-separated list of ids used to filter on tasks that have these order statuses. taskable_type, if provided, can only be 'order' when using this parameter
    + taskable_type (optional, string) - Filter on tasks for orders, customers, or tasks not assigned to either. Valid values are 'order', 'customer', 'none'
    + taskable_id (optional, integer) - Filter on tasks for orders or customers where the taskable id is the id of the order or customer.  taskable type is required when using this parameter
    + due_after (optional, string) - DateTime to filter Tasks with a due date after specified DateTime. Format: ISO8601
    + due_before (optional, string) - DateTime to filter Tasks with a due date before specified DateTime. Format: ISO8601


### Tasks Index [GET]

+ Response 200 (application/json)

    + Headers

            Connection: keep-alive

    + Body

            {
              "meta": {
                "page": 1,
                "per_page": 20,
                "total_count": 25,
                "total_pages": 2
              },
              "data": [
                {
                  "id": 42683,
                  "task_name": "Order more ink for this job",
                  "due_date": "2015-10-13T01:00:00-04:00",
                  "completed_date": null,
